Day 11: Normalisation – 1NF & 2NF

Topic:
Database Normalisation, Data Anomalies, First Normal Form (1NF) and Second Normal Form (2NF)

Learning Objectives:

Understand the purpose of database normalisation
Learn about data anomalies such as insert, update, and delete anomalies
Understand the rules of First Normal Form (1NF) and Second Normal Form (2NF)
Learn how normalization improves database structure and reduces redundancy
Practice organizing data into efficient relational tables

Activities / Deliverables:

Analyse a denormalised employee table
Identify redundancy and data anomalies in the table
Convert the table into First Normal Form (1NF)
Further normalize the structure into Second Normal Form (2NF)
Document each normalization step with explanations and diagrams
Verify the final table structure in MySQL

Tools / Tech:

MySQL
Draw.io

